# Web UI

## Architecture

- **Frontend:** Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite in `frontend/`
- **API:** `ChatHandler` in `src/als_intel/webui.py`
- **Static serving:** `src/als_intel/static_frontend.py` serves `assets/dist/` (SPA)

## Conventions

- UI components live in `frontend/src/components/`; route shells in `frontend/src/views/`
- API client wrappers in `frontend/src/api/`; shared types in `frontend/src/types/`
- i18n source of truth: `src/als_intel/i18n/locales/*.json` (sync via `frontend/scripts/sync-locales.mjs`)
- API responses use `_json_response`; streaming events use `_stream_json_event`
- Auth/CSRF: follow existing protected POST handler patterns; never skip CSRF on authenticated writes
- Extend `tests/test_webui_api.py` for every new or changed API route
- Build frontend before Docker: `make frontend-build` (or multi-stage Dockerfile)

## Dev workflow

```bash
# Terminal 1
make web-dev        # API on :8000 (.venv Python)

# Terminal 2
make frontend-dev   # Vite on :5173, proxies /api to :8000
```

Open `http://localhost:5173/` in dev (not `/app-assets/`). Production builds use `base: /app-assets/` and are served from `assets/dist/`.

Database explorer (`DbExplorerModal.vue`): fixed-height modal, infinite-scroll list, in-modal node detail with source links, reliability breakdowns, and dotted-underline field helpers (`UiFieldHelp`). Result counts use `formatCompactCount()` from `frontend/src/i18n/numbers.ts`.

DB status popover (`DbStatusPopover.vue`, `ManualSyncSourceRow.vue`): compact locale-aware counts and relative timestamps (`formatRelativeTime`, `formatCompactCount`); sync progress shows percent and contextual title; navbar badge shows a spinning sync icon while updating; cooldown button reads "Already up-to-date". Success/error toasts use `last_completion_status` from `/api/sync/manual/status` (not merely "sync stopped").

Manual sync backend (`manual_sync.py`): writes `manual_sync_events` audit rows; exposes `last_completion_status`, `last_completion_error`, and `audit_events` on status API; caps unbounded plan `max_results: 0` jobs via `ALS_MANUAL_SYNC_MAX_RESULTS` (default 250). Source breakdown returns top 5 sources + Others.

## Assistant view

Two-column layout at `lg+` when evidence panel is open: query/report (center) | `EvidenceSidebar` (right). Filters live inline in `AssistantView.vue` above the composer (no left column). Below `lg`, evidence nodes open via `EvidenceSidebarDrawer` toggle.

**Evidence filters** (`FilterPanel.vue` in `AssistantView.vue`): toggle chips for evidence types (`app.evidence_types_to_include`); min reliability, publication date, and highlight contradictions share a compact aligned row on `md+`; changes apply immediately (no Apply button). Collapsible via filter icon button (`filter_list`) + `app.filtersCollapsed`. Ghost **Reset filters** (`app.reset_filters`) restores `DEFAULT_FILTERS` (observational + interventional, 60% reliability, contradictions on). Filters are sent on the next chat stream (`useChatStream.ts` → `filters: app.filters`).

**Query / report** (`AssistantView.vue`, `StreamReport.vue`, `ReportActions.vue`): synthesis report and session actions appear only after first user message or loaded session. Session actions use `app.*` i18n keys; copy success uses `app.citations_copied`.

**Evidence sidebar** (`EvidenceSidebar.vue`): collapsible via `UiDisclosure` + `app.evidenceCollapsed` (default open). When collapsed on `lg+`, the third grid column is removed so the query column expands; reopen via the **Evidence Nodes** button in `AssistantView.vue`. Idle hint before first query (`app.evidence_hint_idle`); empty hint when report has zero cited rows (`app.evidence_hint_empty`). Contradiction highlighting/sorting follows `app.filters.highlight_contradictions` in `EvidenceRow.vue` / `EvidenceList.vue`.

Settings (`SettingsDrawer.vue`): editable section (language, temperature/timeout sliders with visible helper text); read-only section (model, host, context limit from `/api/status`). Shared form primitives: `UiInput`, `UiSelect`, `UiSliderField`. `status` store seeds `app.config` once from `/api/status` on first refresh.
